OL,7,F"It is not a case in which there was
OL,8,Fgross driving, it is not a case in
OL,9,Fwhich there was intoxication or a case
OL,10,Fwhere there was speed, or where there
OL,11,Fwas a dangerous manoeuvre."
OL,13,FThe three judges dismissed the appeal
OL,14,Fbid. They stated that Layton's death
OL,15,Fwas "devastating for the victim's
OL,16,Ffamily" and described the sentencing
OL,17,Fjudge's approach as "conspicuously
OL,18,Fclear, thoughtful and thorough".
